  "prompt": "Up to what rank in GATE ECE can we expect a call from BARC for an interview?",
  "response": "The Bhabha Atomic Research Centre (BARC) typically calls candidates for interviews based on their GATE scores, and the cutoff rank can vary each year depending on several factors such as the number of applicants, the difficulty level of the GATE exam, and the specific requirements of BARC that year.\n\nHistorically, candidates with GATE ranks up to around 1000 to 1500 in the Electronics and Communication Engineering (ECE) category have been called for interviews. However, it's important to note that these numbers are only indicative and can change annually. For the most accurate and up-to-date information, you should refer to BARC's official notifications or contact them directly regarding their selection process for the current year.",
